    thinking: "**Examining Backend Integration**\n\nI\'m now diving into the Express server\'s integration with Vite, specifically how it currently handles API requests. I need to figure out if there are custom environments to work with or if I should consider creating some. This will inform my implementation strategy for the backend.\n\n\n**Implementing Server Functionality**\n\nI\'ve just finished outlining the structure for the `server.ts` file, and I\'m ready to write the robust server code. I\'m focusing on creating that `/api/trainer` endpoint, which will handle POST requests with user questions and contexts, and route the prompt to the Gemini API using the specified system prompt and model name. I\'m also preparing to integrate error handling for compliance, including the required `GEMINI_API_KEY` from the environment.\n\n\n**Prioritizing API Routing**\n\nI\'m now focusing on how to get the `/api/trainer` route working correctly in the backend. I have a clear plan for the server structure in `server.ts`. The implementation will utilize lazy initialization of the Gemini API client. I\'ve considered that the `GEMINI_API_KEY` might not be available, so the client code will provide a fallback message to the frontend, instead of crashing on startup.\n\n\n**Refining Endpoint Logic**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `/api/trainer` endpoint logic. I\'m focusing on validating the incoming request for a question and structuring the prompt based on the context. If no context exists, the user\'s question will be the prompt. I\'m working to retrieve the Gemini client, and construct the prompt using `generateContent` with the flash model, while constructing the system instruction. I\'m also planning to handle errors for when questions are missing.\n\n\n**Constructing Prompt Responses**\n\nI\'m now integrating the Gemini API response handling. I\'ve set up the system instruction to be concise, motivational, and practical. I\'m aiming for responses under 120 words. I\'m ready to handle the potential errors, providing a user-friendly fallback if the `GEMINI_API_KEY` is missing or invalid.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/server.ts` server entry point file. It handles the `/api/trainer` endpoint using the modern `@google/genai` SDK and compiles down into our full-stack server with Vite integrated middleware for running our SPA locally on dev/production."
    thinking_duration {
