  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Program Import**\n\nOkay, I\'ve tracked the `WEEKLY_PROGRAM` variable. It\'s imported just once in `src/App.tsx`, specifically on line 3. It\'s then directly passed as a prop, named `weeklyProgram`, to the `ProgramView` component on line 139. I\'m starting to think about ways to make it more dynamic.\n\n\n**Designing User Profiles**\n\nI\'m now focusing on designing weekly programs and user profiles. My plan involves creating elegant programs for five specialties: Beginners, Weight Loss, Bodybuilder, Powerlifter, and Athletic. I will analyze the current `/src/data.ts` file to understand the existing user profile fields, such as `name`, `level`, and `weightProgress`, and consider how to enhance or integrate these fields with the new program designs.\n\n\n**Implementing Split Selector**\n\nOkay, I\'m now zeroing in on the user interface for selecting workout splits. My idea is to integrate a \"Split Selector\" tab bar directly within `ProgramView.tsx`. This will allow users to seamlessly switch between the different training focuses such as Beginners, Weight Loss, Bodybuilder, Powerlifter, and Athletic. This direct approach directly addresses the user\'s need for a personalized and interactive program selection experience, allowing instant view of the 7-day routine.\n\n\n**Synchronizing Profile and Program**\n\nI\'m now integrating profile updates with program changes to keep user data in sync, a personalized approach to fitness goals. I plan to pass both `profile` and `setProfile` to `ProgramView` to allow users to update their fitness goals directly from the `ProgramView.tsx` component. This will allow a unified, and beautiful interface. I\'m now structuring the `WEEKLY_PROGRAMS` in `/src/data.ts` to support this dynamic behavior, reviewing the existing `WorkoutDay` interface for structure. I\'m taking a detail-oriented approach.\n\n\n**Detailing Powerlifter Split**\n\nI\'m deep in the process of defining the \'Powerlifter\' split, meticulously detailing each day\'s workout. I\'ve outlined Monday with heavy squats, Tuesday focusing on bench press intensity, and Wednesday dedicated to active mobility and lower-back decompression. Now I\'m working on Thursday\'s conventional deadlift intensity, ensuring a balanced, comprehensive program. My goal is to maximize strength and CNS activation, optimizing training for peak performance.\n\n\n**Defining Powerlifter Schedule**\n\nI\'ve finalized Thursday\'s deadlift regime, incorporating conventional and deficit deadlifts. I\'m building Friday\'s routine now, with push-press, dumbbell rows, and curls. Saturday is all about speed squats and bench presses with kettlebell swings for hip connection, and finally, Sunday is a heavy rest day. The goal is to maximize strength and CNS activation across all days.\n\n\n**Structuring Bodybuilder Split**\n\nI\'m now detailing a Bodybuilder split, working on the optimal structure for muscle hypertrophy. I\'m starting with a focus on a comprehensive Monday Chest workout, followed by Tuesday\'s back and biceps. Wednesday will be dedicated to active recovery with core work. I\'m planning out quad dominant burn day, and my idea is to include detailed exercises for each muscle group.\n\n\n**Defining Beginners Split**\n\nI\'m now outlining a \"Beginners Split,\" focused on building a solid foundation. Monday will start with a full-body routine emphasizing form with goblet squats, push-ups (or knee push-ups), inverted rows, and bird-dogs for core stability. Tuesday will then focus on active recovery with a brisk walk. I am planning the rest of the week, with an emphasis on proper form and controlled movements.\n\n\n**Outlining Beginners Week**\n\nI\'ve crafted a \'Beginners Split\' week, and am now refining the mid-week routines. I\'ve designed Full Body B with Romanian Deadlifts, seated dumbbell overhead press, and lat pulldowns. I am incorporating active recovery days with plank holds and low-impact elliptical work. Full Body C features step-ups, dumbbell chest presses, and chest-supported dumbbell rows.\n\n\n**Defining Weight Loss**\n\nI\'m now detailing the \"Weight Loss\" split, which focuses on high-intensity conditioning. I\'ve structured Monday as a \"Metabolic Shock Circuit\" with exercises like KB swings and burpees. Tuesday combines cardio and core work, and I\'ve designed Wednesday as an active recovery day. Thursday will be Upper Body HIIT. I plan for a balanced, high-impact program. I\'ve added a light facepull exercise. I\'ve designed Sunday as rest and goal review.\n\n\n**Defining Athletic Split**\n\nI\'m now detailing the athletic split, and I\'m focused on developing explosive power and triple extension. I am planning Monday\'s routine to begin with power cleans, with four sets of four reps. I\'m focusing on the triple extension hip drive. I plan for metabolic conditioning in the workout ahead.\n\n\n**Structuring Athletic Split**\n\nI\'ve outlined Monday\'s Athletic split and am now focusing on Tuesday\'s unilateral sport performance and balance training. I\'m prioritizing single-leg Romanian deadlifts and rear-foot elevated split squats for balance. Also I\'ve detailed pull-ups, and plank shoulder taps for overall stability. I\'m carefully structuring the week for optimal athletic development.\n\n\n**Refining Athletic Routine**\n\nI\'m now detailing Friday\'s rotational power exercises, including cable woodchops, dumbbell push presses, and incline dumbbell rows, focusing on explosive control. I\'m also planning Saturday\'s conditioning with assault bike intervals and kettlebell snatches to build the aerobic power engine. Sunday will be for rest and athletic restoration. I will verify how to replace `WEEKLY_PROGRAM` with `WEEKLY_PROGRAMS` in `src/data.ts`.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 20
      nanos: 317891955
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
